On 9/3/03 12:07 AM, "Leon Breward" <breward_kenya(-at-)yahoo.co.uk> wrote:

> I have to change all the rubber boots on the cv joints on my bus which I use
> on dirt roads in Kenya. I hate the allen key / hex bolts in there. The socket
> slips, I bust my knuckles and if I'm out from base there is no-one with the
> tools to remove them. Can I change them to ordinary bolts???? What should I
> look out for? any warnings if I try to do this.

You need a grade 10.9 bolt with threads that don't rust (black anodized
etc). M8x48 1.25 pitch (24mm of threads). That style just happens to come in
the hex cap variety more often than not...

